sentences: Mary O'Hara (born 12 May 1935) is an Irish soprano and harpist from County Sligo.
In his autobiography Memoirs of an Irish Troubadour (2002), Liam Clancy wrote how her music inspired and influenced him and others of the Folk Revival period.

O'Hara's initial rise to a high-profile was repeated in 1974 when she left the monastery for the sake of her health, found that her musical reputation had grown during her time in the cloister, and returned to performing.
She continued her singing career for a further 16 years, retiring from performing in 1994.
